tool_description: UP is a wristband and app that tracks how you sleep, move and eat—then helps you use that information to feel your best.  The UP Platform documentation provides information related to establishing and maintaining an API connection with UP. The purpose of this API is to enable the exchange of select data in order to extend and augment the UP user experience and support complementary services. This can include data aggregation and visualization, gaming, marketing, rewards provisioning, and more.
name: Jawbone UP
title: Jawbone UP

api_list.name: Get a generic event for the user
api_list.description: Returns the list of generic events of the current user. This list can be paginated by date or timestamp.

optional_parameters.name: date
optional_parameters.description: Date, formatted as YYYYMMDD. If omitted, returns the information for today.

optional_parameters.name: page_token
optional_parameters.description: Timestamp used to paginate the list of events. The Developer must use the "next" link provided in the "links" section.

optional_parameters.name: start_time
optional_parameters.description: To be used along with end_time. Epoch timestamp that denotes the start of the time range queried for events.

optional_parameters.name: end_time
optional_parameters.description: To be used with start_time. Epoch timestamp that denotes the end of the time range queried for events.

optional_parameters.name: updated_after
optional_parameters.description: Epoch timestamp to list events that are updated later than the timestamp. To be used with start_time to list events that were completed after said start_time.

optional_parameters.name: limit
optional_parameters.description: Maximum number of results to return

import requests

url = "https://community-jawbone-up.p.rapidapi.com/users/@me"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "community-jawbone-up.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())

api_list.name: Get sleep phases
api_list.description: A sleep period can be sub-divided into phases: awake, light and deep. This endpoint returns a time-series of the sleep phase during the period. Each entry is a tuple that contains a timestamp and the sleep phase (1=awake, 2=light, 3=deep). The timestamps are distributed based on when the type of sleep changes.

api_list.name: Get move intensity
api_list.description: Returns a time-series of the move intensity during the day. Each entry is a tuple that contains a timestamp, and the average intensity during that period. Currently, it’s an arbitrary equidistributed list of timestamps.

api_list.name: Get the user's moves list
api_list.description: Returns the list of moves of the current user. This list can be paginated by date or timestamp.

optional_parameters.name: date
optional_parameters.description: Date, formatted as YYYYMMDD. If omitted, returns the information for today.

optional_parameters.name: page_token
optional_parameters.description: Timestamp used to paginate the list of moves. The Developer must use the “next” link provided in the “links” section.

optional_parameters.name: start_time
optional_parameters.description: To be used along with end_time. Epoch timestamp that denotes the start of the time range queried for move events.

optional_parameters.name: end_time
optional_parameters.description: To be used with start_time. Epoch timestamp that denotes the end of the time range queried for move events.

optional_parameters.name: updated_after
optional_parameters.description: Epoch timestamp to list move events that are updated later than the timestamp. To be used with start_time to list events that were completed after said start_time.

api_list.name: Get the user's trends
api_list.description: Returns the user's trends over a period of time (e.g. 5 weeks), using the given granularity (e.g. by day).

optional_parameters.name: end_date
optional_parameters.description: Date, formatted as YYYYMMDD. If omitted, returns until today.

optional_parameters.name: range_duration
optional_parameters.description: Used with range to determine how long to go back in time.

optional_parameters.name: range
optional_parameters.description: Used with range_duration to determine how long to go back in time. Possible values are: d (for “days”) and w (for “weeks”).

optional_parameters.name: bucket_size
optional_parameters.description: Determines the granularity to use when aggregating the values. Possible values are: d (for “days”), w (for “weeks”), m (for “months”), y (for “years”).

api_list.name: Get the user's mood
api_list.description: Returns the user's mood for the given day. Defaults to get today's mood.

optional_parameters.name: date
optional_parameters.description: Date, formatted as YYYYMMDD. If omitted, returns today's mood.
